mqvpn (0.7.0-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Add WRTT (Weighted Round-Trip Time) multipath scheduler: selects paths
    by weight-to-RTT score; RTT acts as tiebreaker when weights are equal;
    spills to secondary paths on cwnd congestion.
  * Add set_path_weight control API command (client): adjust per-path WRTT
    weight at runtime without reconnecting (range 0–65535; 0 = default/1).
  * Raise MQVPN_MAX_PATHS cap from 4 to 8.
  * fix(control): emit n_paths field in per-client get_status JSON response.
  * fix(build): bump libmqvpn soversion for path ABI change.
  * fix(build): forward-declare struct event_base in control_socket.h.
  * Add test_control_response_bound unit test (worst-case JSON fits buffer).
  * Add test_cli_path_argv shell test (8-path CLI argv overflow guard).

 -- mqvpn maintainers <maintainers@example.com>  Thu, 04 Jun 2026 00:00:00 +0000

mqvpn (0.6.0-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Add configurable TUN MTU via --mtu CLI flag and INI/JSON config; cap
    server per-client MTU notification to actual TUN MTU (#131, #132).
  * Add --cc flag for congestion control selection (bbr2, bbr, cubic, none).
  * Add wlb_udp_pin scheduler support (#140).
  * Add routes management option (#143).
  * Fix failover storm crash and add dynamic path budget expansion.
  * Fix always reconnect on path_id=0 removal; fix double-rotation.
  * Fix xqc_conn_close_path() failure when removing path_id=0.
  * Fix path add/remove race.
  * Fix JSON MTU upper bound to match INI parser (65535 → 9000).
  * Raise max_path_id_grant_max_value from 64 to 128; bump xquic submodule
    for reciprocal MAX_PATH_ID fix.

 -- mqvpn maintainers <maintainers@example.com>  Mon, 01 Jun 2026 00:00:00 +0000

mqvpn (0.5.0-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Add QUIC draft-21 support (phase 1, #124).
  * Add path FSM refactor: pre-active split, closed split, path add with
    outcome, platform event API, and Linux external state removal (#88,
    #112, #113, #115, #116, #117).
  * Add support for up to 8 simultaneous paths (xquic limit).
  * Fix control socket handling and add unit test.
  * Fix get_interest timer extension (next_timer_ms only shortened, not
    extended).
  * Fix initial path removal regression and related tests.
  * Fix path_stable_since_us re-arm per RFC spec §6.3; add
    xqc_find_path_metrics helper.
  * Fix multipath not enabled when only --control-port is set.
  * Restore add_path / remove_path / list_paths control API commands.

 -- mqvpn maintainers <maintainers@example.com>  Sun, 18 May 2026 00:00:00 +0000

mqvpn (0.4.2-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Fix server crash (SIGSEGV) when a non-H3 QUIC probe connects without
    a matching ALPN — cb_write_socket and cb_path_removed blindly cast
    mqvpn_server_t * to svr_conn_t * before H3 setup (issue #4282).
  * Fix client busy-loop on -XQC_EMP_CREATE_PATH: close path permanently
    instead of scheduling retries that can never succeed (OOM / cap hit).
  * Fix netlink try_readd busy-loop during WiFi reassociation bursts.
  * client: abort QUIC handshake after 5 s stall and rotate primary path.
  * client: rotate primary path on reconnect to escape stale connections.
  * Control API: unify listen address as "addr:port" via control_listen in
    INI ([Control] Listen) and JSON (control_listen); legacy Port/Addr keys
    remain supported for backward compatibility.
  * Add fixed (pinned) per-user IP address support (server-side).
  * Add congestion control setting in INI config file.
  * Add unit test for server crash regression (non-H3 probe).
  * Windows client support.

